---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home Loan Balance Transfer - Save Lakhs on Interest | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Home Loan Balance Transfer</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Home Loan Balance Transfer</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Transfer your existing home loan to a bank offering lower interest rates and save up to ₹12 lakhs over the remaining tenure. Compare balance transfer offers from 40+ banks with rates starting at 8.25% p.a. Free, instant comparison with no obligation.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Save Up to 2% on Rate</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Save ₹3L - ₹12L on Interest</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
          <span>Processing: 7-15 Days</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Home Loan Balance Transfer?</h2>
          <p>A home loan balance transfer (also called refinancing) involves shifting your outstanding home loan from your current lender to a new bank that offers a lower interest rate. Given that home loans are large (₹30 lakhs to ₹2 crore+) and long-term (15-30 years), even a small reduction in interest rate can result in savings of several lakhs of rupees. For example, transferring a ₹60 lakh loan with 18 years remaining from 9.5% to 8.5% saves approximately ₹5.8 lakhs in interest.</p>
          <p>TrueCred Loan Expert simplifies the home loan balance transfer process by comparing offers from 40+ banks and housing finance companies. We calculate your exact savings after accounting for all charges — foreclosure fee, processing fee, legal and technical charges, and MODT/stamp duty. Our dedicated home loan experts handle the entire process end-to-end, from application to new loan disbursal, ensuring a smooth and hassle-free experience.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.25%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lowest BT Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹12 Lakh</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Savings Possible</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">7-15 Days</span>
              <span class="info-label">Processing Time</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Home Loan Balance Transfer Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>8.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.35%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bank of Baroda</td>
                <td>8.30% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.25%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Ltd</td>
                <td>8.35% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>8.40% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>PNB Housing</td>
                <td>8.45% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>25 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Existing home loan with at least 12 EMIs paid on time</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Outstanding loan balance of at least ₹5,00,000</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 700 or above at the time of balance transfer application</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> No missed or delayed EMI payments in the last 24 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property should be legally clear and approved by the new bank</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Rate difference of at least 0.50% between current and new rate for net savings</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Transfer Your Home Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Calculate Savings</h4>
              <p>Enter your current home loan details — outstanding amount, interest rate, remaining tenure — in our BT savings calculator.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Compare BT Offers</h4>
              <p>We show you offers from 40+ banks with exact savings after all charges. Choose the most beneficial option for your situation.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Initiate Transfer</h4>
              <p>Apply through TrueCred. The new bank handles property verification, legal check, and coordinates with your existing lender for NOC.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Start Saving</h4>
              <p>Once the transfer is complete, your new lower EMI kicks in. Also get an option for top-up loan at the new lower rate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Existing home loan account statement with amortization schedule</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property documents — original sale deed, title documents, and all builder agreements</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Latest property valuation report (the new bank may arrange their own)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Foreclosure letter from existing bank with outstanding amount</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 12 months bank statements showing EMI debits</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income documents — latest salary slips, ITR, and Form 16 (for eligibility reassessment)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Calculate BT Savings</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="7500000">₹75,00,000</option>
                  <option value="10000000">₹1,00,00,000</option>
                  <option value="15000000">₹1,50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="20000000">₹2,00,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about home loan balance transfer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            When is the best time to do a home loan balance transfer?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              The best time is early in your loan tenure (within the first 10-15 years) when you're paying more interest than principal. After this point, savings diminish significantly. Also transfer when: the rate gap is at least 0.50%, your credit score has improved, market rates have dropped, or your existing bank refuses to match competitor rates. Avoid transferring in the last 5 years of your loan.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What charges are involved in a home loan balance transfer?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Charges include: (a) Foreclosure penalty by existing bank — as per RBI rules, no foreclosure charge on floating rate home loans for individuals, (b) Processing fee by new bank — 0.25% to 0.50%, (c) Legal and technical fees — ₹5,000 to ₹15,000, (d) MODT/stamp duty for new mortgage — varies by state (0.1% to 1%), (e) Insurance premiums if applicable. TrueCred calculates net savings after all charges.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a top-up loan along with the balance transfer?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, most banks offer a top-up loan along with the home loan balance transfer. This is one of the biggest advantages of BT — you can access additional funds at home loan rates (8-10% p.a.) instead of taking a separate personal loan at 12-16% p.a. Top-up amounts depend on the property value, your income, and the existing outstanding amount. Common uses include renovation, furnishing, or other personal expenses.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Will my property documents need to be submitted again?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, the new bank will require original property documents for their legal and technical verification. Your existing bank will release the originals after receiving foreclosure payment. This process usually takes 15-30 days. Some banks allow the new bank to directly collect documents from the existing bank to speed up the process. TrueCred coordinates this seamlessly.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Does a home loan balance transfer affect my tax benefits?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              No, transferring your home loan does not affect your tax benefits under Section 24(b) for interest (up to ₹2 lakh) or Section 80C for principal repayment (up to ₹1.5 lakh). The deduction continues seamlessly with the new lender. In fact, since you'll be paying lower interest, you may need to adjust your tax planning. The name on the loan certificate from the new bank remains the same.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Save Lakhs by Transferring Your Home Loan</h3>
          <p>Compare offers from 40+ banks. Zero foreclosure charge on floating rate loans. Save up to ₹12 lakhs.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
